# Markdown Frontmatter Standard

Every `.md` file in this repository **must** begin with a YAML frontmatter block.

## Required Format

```yaml
---
title: "Human-readable document title"
tags: [tag1, tag2, tag3]
aliases: [alternative-name, short-name]
---
```

## Rules

- `title` — sentence-case, matches the first `#` heading
- `tags` — lowercase, hyphen-separated, 2–6 tags from the taxonomy below
- `aliases` — lowercase, hyphen-separated alternative names for Obsidian linking

## Tag Taxonomy

| Category | Tags |
|---|---|
| Type | `experiment`, `analysis`, `results`, `project`, `research`, `readme`, `roadmap` |
| Domain | `llm-behavior`, `rag`, `agents`, `production`, `transformer`, `llm-internals` |
| Topic | `temperature`, `system-prompt`, `token-limit`, `attention`, `embeddings`, `evaluation` |
| Meta | `portfolio`, `insights`, `papers`, `concepts`, `learning-path` |

## Examples

**Experiment file:**
```yaml
---
title: "Experiment 05 — Embeddings"
tags: [experiment, embeddings, llm-internals, analysis]
aliases: [embeddings-experiment, exp-05]
---
```

**Project README:**
```yaml
---
title: "Project — RAG Assistant"
tags: [project, rag, retrieval, llm]
aliases: [rag-assistant]
---
```

**Research note:**
```yaml
---
title: "Research — Scaling Laws"
tags: [research, papers, scaling-laws, llm-internals]
aliases: [scaling-laws, kaplan-2020]
---
```

## Idempotency

- Never add a second frontmatter block if one already exists (check `startswith("---")`)
- When editing an existing file, update the frontmatter tags if new topics are covered
